## 6. Backend: Supabase Edge Functions (Deno)

### `supabase/functions/detect-phishing/index.ts` (1683 lines)

The server-side detection engine. Runs in **Deno** on Supabase infrastructure.

**Key Analysis Modules:**

| Module | What It Does |
|---|---|
| Rate Limiting | 20 req/min per IP, auto-cleanup |
| Input Validation | 50KB max, type detection (URL/email/SMS) |
| `analyzeUrl()` | IP-URL, suspicious TLD, deep subdomains, entropy, homograph detection |
| `detectLookalikeAttack()` | Character substitution with `LOOKALIKE_SUBSTITUTIONS` map |
| `detectHomographAttack()` | Unicode lookalike (Cyrillic/Greek characters) |
| `checkTyposquatting()` | Brand-pattern matching (amazon-secure, paypal-login, etc.) |
| `analyzeEmailHeaders()` | From/Reply-To mismatch, free email provider spoofing |
| `analyzeSubjectLine()` | Phishing keywords in subject header |
| `checkGenericGreetings()` | "Dear Customer", "Dear Valued Member" patterns |
| `checkAttachmentRisks()` | `.exe`, `.docm`, `.ps1`, macro file references |
| `analyzeUrlsAndContent()` | Deep per-URL lookalike + hidden link + shortener analysis |
| `heuristicAnalysis()` | Grammar errors, fake SSL claims, urgency score, fear tactics |
| `behavioralAnalysis()` | Mismatched links, unusual payment requests, time pressure |
| `analyzeHtmlPatterns()` | Embedded forms, hidden links, image-only emails |
| `analyzeText()` | Scam patterns, credential request patterns |
| **PhishTank API** | Community-verified phishing URL database check |
| **Google Safe Browsing API** | Google's real-time threat list (v4) |

**Detection Score → Label mapping:**
- `0–19` → ✅ Safe
- `20–49` → ⚡ Suspicious  
- `50+` → 🚨 Phishing

### `supabase/functions/extract-email-from-pdf/index.ts`
Extracts email content from uploaded PDF files for analysis.

### `supabase/functions/extract-urls-from-image/index.ts`
Performs OCR on uploaded screenshots to extract URLs/text for analysis.

### `supabase/functions/_schemas.ts`
Shared Zod validation schemas used to parse AI model responses consistently.

