## 9. Database (Supabase PostgreSQL)

### `scan_history` Table
| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `id` | UUID | Primary key |
| `user_id` | UUID | FK → auth.users (nullable for anonymous) |
| `content` | TEXT | Scanned input |
| `input_type` | TEXT | url / email / sms |
| `label` | TEXT | safe / suspicious / phishing |
| `risk_percentage` | NUMERIC | 0–100 |
| `confidence` | NUMERIC | 0–1 |
| `top_reasons` | TEXT[] | Array of flagged reasons |
| `details` | JSONB | Full indicators + analysis_summary |
| `created_at` | TIMESTAMPTZ | Scan timestamp |

**Row Level Security (RLS):** Users can only read/write their own rows.

